The paper deals with algorithms and data structures for networks, which suggests that it belongs to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories. However, the focus on time-dependent min-cost path metrics and the mention of Dijkstra-Rank suggest that it is more likely to belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category. Within this category, the paper deals with hierarchical oracles, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) or Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI) categories. Finally, the mention of subquadratic preprocessing time and sublinear query time suggests that it could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category.
